text: Sarchehan County () is a county in Fars Province, Iran. At the 2006 census, its population was 18,933, in 4,569 families. The county has two cities, Korehi & Hesami, and three rural districts (dehestan): Bagh Safa Rural District, Sarchehan Rural District, and Tujerdi Rural District. The Sarchehan County was established on 2018 in Fars province. == References == Category:Counties in Fars Province Category:Establishments in Iran Category:2018 establishments in Asia
